'''Nizar Mahmoud Ahmed Al-Rashdan''' ({{langx|ar|نزار الرشدان}}; born 23 March 1999) is a Jordanian professional footballer who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Qatar SC|Qatar]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
Al-Rashdan began his senior career with [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] in the [[Jordanian Pro League]] in 2019. On 4 January 2021, he transferred to [[Al-Faisaly SC|Al-Faisaly]] on a 2-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jawharatarabnews.net/article/49188|title=رسمياً- الفيصلي يتعاقد مع نزار الرشدان|website=جوهة العرب}}</ref> He extended his contract for 2 more season on 11 January 2014 after helping the club win the [[2022 Jordanian Pro League]], [[Jordan FA Cup|2021 Jordan FA Cup]], and the 2022 [[Jordan Shield Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1204491|title=الفيصلي الأردني يجدد عقد الرشدان|date=January 11, 2023|website=كووورة}}</ref> On 14 January 2023 he went on a half-season loan to the [[Iraq Stars League]] club [[Newroz SC|Newroz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1205433|title=نجم الفيصلي يرحل للدوري العراقي|date=January 14, 2023|website=كووورة}}</ref> On 31 July 2024, Nizar signed with [[Bahraini Premier League]] side [[Al-Khaldiya SC|Al-Khaldiya]] on a permanent transfer, around US$200 thousand.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abdullah |first1=Waleed |title=الخالدية يعلن رسميا عن ضم الأردني نزار الرشدان |url=https://alwatannews.net/Sports/article/1118866/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D9%86-%D8%B6%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%86%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%B4%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86 |website=alwatannews.net |publisher=Al-Watan |language=Arabic |date=31 July 2024}}</ref> On 28 July 2025, Al-Rashdan returned to Iraq to join [[Al-Zawraa SC|Al-Zawraa]] for one season, with an option for an additional season.<ref>{{cite web |title=الأردني نزار الرشدان ينضم لصفوف الزوراء |url=https://ina.iq/ar/sport/239687-.html |website=ina.iq |publisher=Iraqi News Agency |access-date=28 July 2025 |language=Arabic |date=28 July 2025}}</ref> On 8 January 2026, [[Qatar SC|Qatar]] announced the signing of Al-Rashdan for half a season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hassan |first1=Fayez |title=بعد انضمامه لنادي قطر.. الرشدان يدخل التشكيل الأساسي ضد السد |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B6%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87-%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%B4%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%AE%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B6%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AF |website=winwin.com |publisher=WinWIn |access-date=30 January 2026 |language=Arabic |date=8 January 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Al-Rashdan was first called up to the senior [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] in a friendly 2–0 win over [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] on 4 September 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/31746/Jordan_Haiti.html|title=Jordan vs. Haiti|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref> He was called up to the national team for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1294093|title=منتخب الأردن يستدعي أبو حشيش|date=December 19, 2023|website=كووورة}}</ref> On 29 January 2024, he scored the winning goal in a 3–2 victory over [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], which qualified his country to the Asian tournament's quarter-final.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/jordan-leave-it-late-beat-iraq-3-2-reach-asian-cup-quarter-finals-2024-01-29/ |title=Jordan leave it late to beat Iraq 3–2 and reach Asian Cup quarter-finals |publisher=Reuters |date=29 January 2024 }}</ref>

